<br>
I would like to see a bindstone, a seige merchant, and a porter to Fort Sauvage.  Having the seige merchant allows us to purchase trebs as well as rams, so it has it's advantages.  Depending upon someone to build 'ram parts' and place them in the vault I can forsee causing problems.<br>
<br>
Porting to GH for regular RvRing is truly a pain in the ass.  It adds additional time and inevitably causes groups to have to wait for additonal ports.  As it stands now, I keep both bound at FS because it's still much easier.  If we do have an event that requires us to be in SI, one long horse ride is much better than messing with the 'numbnut' porter in Goth Harbour five times a night &lt;give or take&gt;.<br>
<br>
I also like the idea of alchemist there as well, but am not exposed to whether we can buy products from someone who holds the items themselves....or is that the porch merchant?<br>
<br>
I wouldn't really worry about a Snow portal at this point.  And if we do go with a FS porter, we can always grab a horse to Snow from there.<br>
<br>
As far as a healer goes, I don't see it as a huge priority.  Most of the time, you are waiting long enough for a port that time is ticking off that release effects anyways or you stop and rebuff for timers anyways.  In all fairness though, both my characters don't really suffer much from rez/release effects.<br>
<br>
If we don't need the Apprentice Tradeskills Merchant for much, then I would much rather see BK Porter to FS.<br>
<br>
I agree a porch would be nice.  Personally I don't think a Lathe is a must-have quite yet.  Fletching is rare and I really don't mind going to Diogel to do the orders.  Or worse running Dulcette to Camelot with the required items to make things.  I see it as something down the road, but a forge has a much greater need, just from a /salvage alone stand point.<br>
<br>
Decorations:  Upgrading guild flags.  Large gathering table would be nice.  Maybe a couple of chairs and a rug upon entry just so it doesn't look empty.  The rest we can get as we gather more funds.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
