<br>
Guild House (Nappa 9)<br>
<br>
1 Spellcraft Merchant<br>
2 Grandmaster Tradeskills Merchant <br>
3 Goth Harbor Porter<br>
4 Alb Vault <br>
<br>
Cottage (Nappa 10)<br>
1 Alb Vault and/or Healer<br>
2 Siege Merchant<br>
3 Border Keep Porter<br>
<br>
<br>
Cottage (Kingsdale 1)<br>
1 Alchemy Merchant 1 (poison and potion)<br>
2 Alchemy Merchant 2 (potion, tincture, enchantment)<br>
3 Alchemy Merchant 3 (dye, tincture, enchantment)<br>
<br>
Siege Merchants have all the construction components on them as well as the items themselves, ergo if you want to make siege equipment or just buy the stuff, a siege merchant covers both bills.<br>
<br>
Also, this theory removes the low-end materials merchant and causes the purchase of another spellcraft/alc table and gets 3 of the 4 alc merchants (so if you want to dyes, you may be out of luck).  We can purchase the low-end materials merchant and vault him if we think there's sufficient reason to -have- one besides using it to build siege equipment.<br>
